concept_explanation.prefix_sum:
**Prefix sum — precompute, query in O(1):**

```java
// Build: O(n)
int[] prefix = new int[n + 1]; // prefix[0] = 0
for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) prefix[i+1] = prefix[i] + nums[i];

// Query rangeSum(l, r) — 0-indexed, inclusive: O(1)
int rangeSum = prefix[r+1] - prefix[l];
// prefix[r+1] = sum of nums[0..r]
// prefix[l]   = sum of nums[0..l-1]
// difference  = sum of nums[l..r]

// Example: nums=[3,1,2,5,8], l=1, r=3
// prefix=[0,3,4,6,11,19]
// rangeSum(1,3) = prefix[4] - prefix[1] = 11 - 3 = 8
// Verify: 1+2+5 = 8 ✓
```

